Dear Colleague,

The Society for Maternal-Fetal Medicine is pleased to announce that abstract submissions for the 2026 Annual Meeting are now open.

Key dates:

    Submission window opens: August 15, 2026
    Submission deadline: Sunday, November 15, 2026 at 11:59 PM Eastern Time
    Notification of acceptance: January 10, 2027
    Annual Meeting: February 1-6, 2027, Denver, Colorado

Categories accepting submissions include Basic Science, Clinical Research, Health Services Research, Health Equity and Disparities, Educational Research, and Quality Improvement.

Consistent with the Society's IRB umbrella framework, all submitted work must use aggregate-cohort framing. Individual patient case narratives, chart-level detail, and any content that could constitute a re-identification risk are outside the scope of accepted abstracts.

For the Health Equity and Disparities track, we particularly welcome submissions on immigrant maternal outcomes, structural determinants of perinatal disparities, and community-partnered research.

Best regards,

